I don't know what's been wrong with me lately.

28
00:02:28,970 --> 00:02:33,480
I fought with my life's force to be with Brother Xu Chi.

29
00:02:34,790 --> 00:02:36,480
Then it turns out,

30
00:02:37,890 --> 00:02:40,950
I ended up in romantic gossip with a GO God like you.

31
00:02:47,580 --> 00:02:53,010
How can I describe my latest emotional state? It's...

32
00:02:53,010 --> 00:02:57,460
It's really frustrating and sad.

33
00:03:19,280 --> 00:03:20,850
Let me tell you.

34
00:03:20,850 --> 00:03:24,010
I've always thought that Brother Xu Chi and I

35
00:03:24,010 --> 00:03:26,620
were a match made in Heaven,

36
00:03:26,620 --> 00:03:29,350
childhood sweethearts.

37
00:03:29,350 --> 00:03:32,410
Do you know when I started to like him?

38
00:03:33,740 --> 00:03:38,320
Say something! You haven't said a word, leaving me all alone.

39
00:03:38,320 --> 00:03:41,160
Nag, nag, nag,

40
00:03:41,160 --> 00:03:44,730
as if I were drunk.

41
00:03:45,850 --> 00:03:47,820
Okay. When?

42
00:03:48,390 --> 00:03:50,700
In 7th grade.

43
00:03:50,700 --> 00:03:52,760
The school was inspecting our appearance and clothing,

44
00:03:52,760 --> 00:03:57,380
and... we were forbidden to have long hair. Our school's dean

45
00:03:57,380 --> 00:04:00,780
caught me at the entrance of the school.

46
00:04:00,780 --> 00:04:03,720
The second day, at school,

47
00:04:03,720 --> 00:04:07,590
I climbed over the wall to get into the school.

48
00:04:08,450 --> 00:04:10,080
You can climb over walls?

49
00:04:10,080 --> 00:04:13,330
However, as I was going up the wall...

50
00:04:13,330 --> 00:04:16,290
I was able to get on the wall...

51
00:04:16,290 --> 00:04:20,230
but I couldn't get down.

52
00:04:20,230 --> 00:04:22,890
Did Xu Chi help you get down?

53
00:04:22,890 --> 00:04:27,140
I remember it. I remember, that day,

54
00:04:27,140 --> 00:04:30,790
he was wearing a black suit,

55
00:04:30,790 --> 00:04:36,240
the suit had buttons in the front.

56
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:39,440
At that time, he stood

57
00:04:39,440 --> 00:04:43,590
at the bottom of the wall. He looked at me.

58
00:04:43,590 --> 00:04:46,050
He said to me with a smile,

59
00:04:46,700 --> 00:04:51,090
"Zhiliao, come on down.

60
00:04:51,090 --> 00:04:54,600
I'm at the bottom. I'll be like this... I'll be like this...

61
00:04:54,600 --> 00:04:57,280
I'll catch you like this."

62
00:04:57,280 --> 00:05:01,760
The way he was smiling at me, I thought he was especially handsome.

63
00:05:01,760 --> 00:05:06,490
And then I took the initiative,

64
00:05:06,490 --> 00:05:08,140
just like this,

65
00:05:09,360 --> 00:05:12,160
I jumped into his embrace.

66
00:05:12,160 --> 00:05:14,520
But I didn't jump well,

67
00:05:14,520 --> 00:05:18,860
so we both fell. I thought his immediate reaction

68
00:05:18,860 --> 00:05:21,220
would be... to push me away.

69
00:05:21,220 --> 00:05:26,590
And then, he didn't do that. He hugged me tightly.

70
00:05:27,970 --> 00:05:29,720
And then,

71
00:05:31,060 --> 00:05:34,960
he told me, "Zhiliao...

72
00:05:35,860 --> 00:05:38,840
Zhiliao, are you in pain from the fall?"

73
00:05:41,120 --> 00:05:43,770
After all these years,

74
00:05:43,770 --> 00:05:46,590
that one sentence,

75
00:05:46,590 --> 00:05:49,430
I've always remembered it.

76
00:05:49,430 --> 00:05:51,870
Every year, he would come back for the holidays

77
00:05:51,870 --> 00:05:53,960
and take me out to have fun.

78
00:05:53,960 --> 00:05:58,040
And whatever requests I had,

79
00:05:58,040 --> 00:06:02,440
any requests, he would always say yes to.

80
00:06:03,610 --> 00:06:10,850
I really didn't expect that it was my older sister he loved.

81
00:06:10,850 --> 00:06:13,780
Why?

82
00:06:13,780 --> 00:06:18,800
Why wasn't it me that he loved?

83
00:06:18,800 --> 00:06:21,880
Why my sister?

84
00:06:43,940 --> 00:06:46,560
Miss, I can't believe you're up.

85
00:06:46,560 --> 00:06:48,780
Are you hungry? I can make some food for you.

86
00:06:48,780 --> 00:06:51,730
Dad, I haven't brushed my teeth yet.

87
00:06:51,730 --> 00:06:54,440
What celebration party were you at yesterday?

88
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:56,380
How did you get so drunk?

89
00:06:56,380 --> 00:06:58,500
How did I get back?

90
00:06:58,500 --> 00:06:59,990
You came back by yourself.

91
00:06:59,990 --> 00:07:03,590
You knocked on the door so hard that you almost woke up the neighbors.

92
00:07:03,590 --> 00:07:05,550
I came back by myself?

93
00:07:05,560 --> 00:07:08,180
You came back by yourself!

94
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:11,430
- Nobody brought me back?
- Nobody brought you back.

95
00:07:13,410 --> 00:07:16,350
Hungry? I'll go make you some food.

96
00:07:17,340 --> 00:07:19,370
My brain...

97
00:07:33,240 --> 00:07:35,210
I'm hungry.

98
00:07:36,280 --> 00:07:38,540
Is this your home?

99
00:07:50,360 --> 00:07:54,550
This is bad! Very bad!

100
00:08:11,500 --> 00:08:13,500
- Hello?
 - Hello, GO God.

101
00:08:13,500 --> 00:08:16,710
You're awake. Does your head hurt?

102
00:08:16,710 --> 00:08:20,870
A little. Not a big problem.

103
00:08:20,870 --> 00:08:22,690
Have a cup of honey water.

104
00:08:22,690 --> 00:08:27,830
How did I get home last night?

105
00:08:27,830 --> 00:08:30,100
I brought you home.

106
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:33,610
But when I got to your door,

107
00:08:33,610 --> 00:08:36,550
you pushed me out and insisted on knocking on the door yourself.

108
00:08:36,550 --> 00:08:40,160
Daddy, open up!

109
00:08:40,850 --> 00:08:43,420
Open up!

110
00:08:45,190 --> 00:08:47,890
Did I say anything weird?

111
00:08:47,890 --> 00:08:49,480
No.

112
00:08:50,100 --> 00:08:53,170
Except for telling me the whole story

113
00:08:53,180 --> 00:08:55,330
of how you fell in love with Xu Chi.

114
00:08:55,330 --> 00:09:00,520
Everything that happened yesterday can only be our little secret.

115
00:09:00,520 --> 00:09:02,590
You can't tell anyone else.

116
00:09:02,590 --> 00:09:04,300
Okay.

117
00:09:04,300 --> 00:09:09,250
GO God, thank you for coming to my rescue yesterday.

118
00:09:09,250 --> 00:09:14,910
And also thank you for listening to me talk so much. I have a question.

119
00:09:14,910 --> 00:09:19,760
Other than that, what other embarrassing things did I do?

120
00:09:28,260 --> 00:09:30,620
You threw up everywhere in my house.

121
00:09:30,620 --> 00:09:32,150
Does that count?

122
00:09:32,150 --> 00:09:35,550
I... I'm sorry.

123
00:09:35,550 --> 00:09:37,760
And you...

124
00:09:38,860 --> 00:09:43,340
Okay, we're even now.

125
00:09:43,340 --> 00:09:47,950
Too much had happened last night and I don't know if I can go to work today.

126
00:09:47,950 --> 00:09:51,620
It wasn't that bad. I was messing with you.

127
00:09:51,620 --> 00:09:54,140
There's something else.

128
00:09:54,140 --> 00:09:57,590
From other people's perspectives,

129
00:09:57,590 --> 00:10:00,130
